  "body": "Hi, can anybody tell me what I am doing wrong with connecting to websockets using basic auth ? I have managed to do it via RPC and embedding the user:password in the URL but I don't think is support on protocol ws://\r\n\r\nSo looking through the code I guessed I could do something like the following but I get an error\r\n\r\n```\r\n    rpcClient, err := rpc.Dial(\"ws://geth.mydomain.network:80/ws/\")\r\n    rpcClient.SetHeader(\"Authorization\", \"Basic ABCDEFGHJJJJJJ==\" )\r\n\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatal(err)\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    client := ethclient.NewClient(rpcClient)\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatal(err)\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI get an error on SetHeader like so\r\n\r\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\n[signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x8 pc=0x435b546]\r\n\r\ngoroutine 1 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/rpc.(*Client).SetHeader(0x0, 0x46bb387, 0xd, 0x46c76c9, 0x1e)\r\n        /Users/ian/.gvm/pkgsets/go1.16.4/global/pkg/mod/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum@v1.10.3/rpc/client.go:267 +0x26\r\nmain.main()\r\n        /Users/ian/Development/Personal/coininfo/go/test/main.go:18 +0xed\r\nexit status 2\r\n\r\n\r\nI am obviously not doing it right :frowning:\r\n\r\nCan anyone lend a hand ?\r\n\r\nI did the above because ethClient doesn't seem to accept headers or anything - so i can't pass in basic auth. I am a little lost.\r\nThis seems to be the line in the go-ethereum code base that it's indicating.\r\n\r\n    if !c.isHTTP {\r\n        return\r\n    }\r\n\r\nI think I am missing a step or I have done it completely wrong.\r\n\r\nI could not find any examples anywhere - are there any ?\r\nJust to make my question completely. I have nginx in front of the geth node. Using the url for \r\nhttp://user:password@somedomain.com/rpc\r\n\r\nworks great. but this is not websockets.\r\n\r\nThanks in advance.\r\n",
